---
/**
 * VerifyLoop
 *
 * Canvas schematic of the submit-and-verify hand-off. The main thread runs a
 * sequence of steps and, at submit, hands off to a separate verifier thread; a
 * pass commits, a fail returns the critique to the thread. Rendering lives in
 * scripts/diagrams/verify-loop.ts; this component is the mount point and the
 * accessible description.
 *
 * Self-contained: takes no props.
 */
---

<figure class="not-prose diagram-figure" aria-labelledby="verify-loop-caption">
  <canvas
    class="diagram__canvas"
    data-diagram="verify-loop"
    role="img"
    aria-label="The submit-and-verify hand-off."
    aria-describedby="verify-loop-desc"
  ></canvas>
  <figcaption id="verify-loop-caption" class="diagram-caption diagram__caption">
    The main thread hands off to a separate verifier; a pass commits, a fail
    returns the critique to the thread.
  </figcaption>

  <div class="diagram-desc" id="verify-loop-desc">
    The main thread runs a sequence of steps — search, read, reason, submit.
    Submitting hands off to a separate verifier thread that runs with fresh
    context, reviews the proposed result against a rubric, and reaches a
    verdict: a pass commits the result to the knowledge graph; a fail returns
    the critique to the main thread, which tries again.
  </div>
</figure>

<script src="../../scripts/diagrams/verify-loop.ts"></script>

<style>
  .diagram__canvas {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 820 / 300;
  }

  .diagram__caption {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
